Prompt Level: 7.0 Prompt: Your friend is about to open a secondhand clothes shop. He doesn’t have much capital, and is renting a very old building. He has got a few quotes for property and liability insurance, but they have been very high. He asks you to do a risk assessment of the premises. Have a look at your checklist, then write him an email advising him of the changes he has to make. Write 150-200 words. Response: From: Insurance Company
To: Dave´s Old Clothes Emporium.

Dear Mr. Jones, 
In our last visit we can found many problems in the emporium and it should be fixed im 60 days because if not we cannot revenew the insurance.
Find below the issues to be corrected:
OUTSIDE the store:
1) Untidy yard with loose bricks outside in front of the emporium;
2) There are bloched drainpipes, if to rain the drainpipes could not drain the water and this can damage the property;
3) Leaky roof 4 tiles that were broked;
4) Cluttered sidewalk redo because the client can be fall down.
INSIDE the store:
5) Poor lighting, replace with LED bulbs;
6) stacked boxes in a small room without windows and bloched the fire extinguisher;
7) Old fire extinguishers replace for new one.
8) Loose chemicals and many places in the storem this materials should be closed in a separeted room.
